<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - REMOVE - MAIN CASE (FIGURES 50 AND 51)</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="5">
        <title>MAIN CASE (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302250">FIGURES 50</hotlnk>
            AND
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302251">51</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302250" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302250" filename="../figg13/G1302250.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 50. Main Case &#38; Shift Forks</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1302251" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302251" filename="../figg13/G1302251.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 51. Clutch Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four remaining case bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302252">Figure 52</hotlnk>). Next, use pry bars in the milled slots to help separate
                the case from the clutch housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302252" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302252" filename="../figg13/G1302252.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Separate Case From Clutch Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the auxiliary countershaft front bearings are damaged, remove and replace them (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302253">Figure 53</hotlnk>). Also remove the rear countershaft bearing cup races
                before removing the main case. This will prevent them from falling into the transmission.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302253" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302253" filename="../figg13/G1302253.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 53. Replace Worn Countershaft Bearings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the case from the clutch housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302254">Figure 54</hotlnk>). Note that the rear shift bar support bracket remains with
                the case.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302254" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302254" filename="../figg13/G1302254.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Lift Case From Clutch Housing</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When moving heavy parts, use a chain hoist to help prevent personal injury.</para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
